The paper deals with graph algorithms and sparsification, which are topics typically studied in computer science subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and information theory (cs.IT). The use of spectral sparsifiers also involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and the paper presents a new algorithm, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
